            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Crispin<supplied reason="lost">us</supplied> posuit titulum <lb n="2"/>dulcissim<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> coniugi suae <lb n="3"/>Maur<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> qui <note>sic</note> d<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>cretum ge<lb break="no" n="4"/>nesi<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied> conplevit <note>sic</note> quod fui<lb break="no" n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">m</supplied>us <note>sic</note> uno con<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>ugio men<lb break="no" n="6"/>ses X et dies XXVII qui <note>sic</note> vix<supplied reason="lost">it a</supplied>nnis <lb n="7"/>XVII et menses VIIII et dies XX <lb n="8"/>hunc titulum posuit Cris<lb break="no" n="9"/>pinus coniugi suae Maurae <lb n="10"/>in XP<expan><ex>Christ</ex><abbr>o</abbr></expan> IH<expan><ex>s</ex><abbr>u</abbr></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Vier aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten. Paläographie: Vorkarolingische Kapitalis I. Z. 10 (Ende): griechische Buchstaben XPO IHV. (B): Boppert; Kessel: Z. 1: p]osuit; Kessel: Z. 1: ti[it]ulum; Z. 2: dul[c]issi[m]e; Z. 3: [de]cretum; Z. 3/4: ge/nes[is]; Z. 5: con[iu]gio; CIL 13, 11918: Z. 6: XII DIES (Majuskeltext); XII et dies (Transkription); ILCV: Z. 6: XII dies; Kessel: Z. 9: coniungi.</p>
            </div>
